convertFont.py is a program to convert the fonts from the SSD1351 driver
(https://github.com/rdagger/micropython-ssd1351) to a format understood by Peter Hinch's font-to-py library:
https://github.com/peterhinch/micropython-font-to-py

It converts the C code from the ssd1351 driver to Python3 code required by
/micropython-font-to-py

Please call the program as follows:
./convertFont.py name_of_C_File font_width font_height first_char no_of_chars >name_of_Python_output_file